Power – BI Course Content

1. INTRODUCTION TO POWER BI 
• Overview of Power BI  
• Purpose and scope in data analysis and visualization  
• Role of Power BI in the BI ecosystem 

2. DATA TRANSFORMATION 
• Introduction to Power Query Editor  
• Overview of transformation tools 

3. CONNECTING DATA 
• Types of data connection modes: Import, DirectQuery, Live Connection 
• Connecting to different data sources (Excel, SQL Server, CSV, web, etc.) 

4. DATA CLEANING 
• Removing errors and empty values  
• Text operations (split, concatenate, case change, etc.)  
• Number operations (rounding, addition, subtraction, etc.)  
• Date/Time operations (extract, format, manipulate dates)  
• Replace values  
• Merging and splitting columns  
• Pivoting and unpivoting data 

5.Modeling
Creating relationships ,managing it ,understanding schemas etc

6. DAX (DATA ANALYSIS EXPRESSIONS) 
• Introduction to DAX  
• Types of DAX functions (aggregation, time intelligence, logical, etc.)  
• Differences between calculated columns and measures  
• Writing and applying DAX formulas 

7. VISUALIZATION 
• Creating and customizing visualizations (charts, tables, slicers, etc.)  
• Formatting visuals for better insights  
• Using filters and slicers effectively
